00:53:29.450 --> 00:53:32.655
We've got time for one more.

00:53:32.655 --> 00:53:34.030
AUDIENCE: I wanted
to say, I love

00:53:34.030 --> 00:53:36.280
hearing how much you
guys have thought

00:53:36.280 --> 00:53:39.160
about the story and
about character,

00:53:39.160 --> 00:53:42.430
and just how deeply
you're invested in that.

00:53:42.430 --> 00:53:46.330
I just really loved
watching that.

00:53:46.330 --> 00:53:50.380
Kind of a little
bit related to that,

00:53:50.380 --> 00:53:52.840
one of my personal favorite
Superman stories is "Superman--

00:53:52.840 --> 00:53:56.350
Red Son," which for anybody
who doesn't know about that

00:53:56.350 --> 00:53:59.740
is Superman, instead of his
rocket ship crashing in Kansas,

00:53:59.740 --> 00:54:02.590
it crashes in the Soviet Union.

00:54:02.590 --> 00:54:04.900
And he grows up there
instead, and kind of

00:54:04.900 --> 00:54:07.209
like how that transforms
the character.

00:54:07.209 --> 00:54:09.250
I just wanted to know if
you guys have any, like,

00:54:09.250 --> 00:54:12.550
thoughts about that-- about
how that would change Superman

00:54:12.550 --> 00:54:16.040
and what would stay constant
about the character?

00:54:16.040 --> 00:54:17.860
Because what's of
intrinsic to him

00:54:17.860 --> 00:54:21.360
and what he picked up from the
Kents by being raised by them?

00:54:21.360 --> 00:54:21.790
BRIAN MICHAEL
BENDIS: Well, I think

00:54:21.790 --> 00:54:23.373
that's why the
"Elseworlds" in general

00:54:23.373 --> 00:54:29.200
are such a big thing at DC,
because all the characters can

00:54:29.200 --> 00:54:32.499
be shown through these awesome,
like, cracked mirrors and--

00:54:32.499 --> 00:54:33.290
DAN JURGENS: Right.

00:54:33.290 --> 00:54:34.220
BRIAN MICHAEL
BENDIS: Yeah, right?

00:54:34.220 --> 00:54:35.210
You're all done them.

00:54:35.210 --> 00:54:35.440
Yeah.

00:54:35.440 --> 00:54:35.740
PAUL DINI: Yeah.

00:54:35.740 --> 00:54:37.060
BRIAN MICHAEL BENDIS: Right.

00:54:37.060 --> 00:54:39.460
PAUL DINI: Well, I did
one in the animated series

00:54:39.460 --> 00:54:42.160
where he leads an
invasion on Earth

00:54:42.160 --> 00:54:45.190
because he believes that he
was raised on Apocalypse.

00:54:45.190 --> 00:54:50.350
And it was almost like
"The Manchurian Candidate."

00:54:50.350 --> 00:54:51.950
He was attacked in space.

00:54:51.950 --> 00:54:53.920
His memory was
basically blotted out.

00:54:53.920 --> 00:54:55.477
And these other
memories were put

00:54:55.477 --> 00:54:56.935
in that he was the
son of Darkseid,

00:54:56.935 --> 00:55:00.880
that he was found and
brought to Apocalypse.

00:55:00.880 --> 00:55:04.030
And he has a whole history
with Darkseid, which only

00:55:04.030 --> 00:55:05.590
goes back, like, about a week.

00:55:05.590 --> 00:55:07.450
And he leads an
invasion on Earth.

00:55:07.450 --> 00:55:10.090
And that is a very natural
thing for him to do.

00:55:10.090 --> 00:55:15.280
And when he returns,
he is himself again.

00:55:15.280 --> 00:55:16.630
But he's really mad.

00:55:16.630 --> 00:55:18.140
And he goes after Darkseid.

00:55:18.140 --> 00:55:19.720
And Bruce Timm and
I said, this is

00:55:19.720 --> 00:55:22.970
the only time Darkseid will
ever get physical in the show.

00:55:22.970 --> 00:55:25.450
This is the only time
that Superman is so mad

00:55:25.450 --> 00:55:26.770
that he confronts him.

00:55:26.770 --> 00:55:27.340
And he goes.

00:55:27.340 --> 00:55:28.270
And he fights him.

00:55:28.270 --> 00:55:30.700
And Darkseid is forced
to fight physically.

00:55:30.700 --> 00:55:33.480
And Superman beats
him, and he loses.

00:55:33.480 --> 00:55:34.810
And he loses his--

00:55:34.810 --> 00:55:39.100
we wanted it to be a
spiritual defeat for him,

00:55:39.100 --> 00:55:41.590
because he takes Darkseid,
throws him into the street,

00:55:41.590 --> 00:55:44.247
and says to the people of
Apocalypse, you're free.

00:55:44.247 --> 00:55:45.330
And they look at Superman.

00:55:45.330 --> 00:55:46.330
They look at Darkseid.

00:55:46.330 --> 00:55:48.970
And they pick him up, and they
put him back on the throne

00:55:48.970 --> 00:55:50.770
because that's what they know.

00:55:50.770 --> 00:55:53.500
And Superman had to lose it.

00:55:53.500 --> 00:55:54.970
And he had to confront him.

00:55:54.970 --> 00:55:57.190
And he actually starts
to go after him again.

00:55:57.190 --> 00:55:59.590
And Supergirl, who's a part
of the story, says, stop.

00:55:59.590 --> 00:56:01.570
If you go after him,
someone's going to die.

00:56:01.570 --> 00:56:03.220
And it won't be Darkseid.

00:56:03.220 --> 00:56:05.450
And he realizes,
I can't do this.

00:56:05.450 --> 00:56:07.660
I cannot be the liberator.

00:56:07.660 --> 00:56:12.370
I cannot be the guy
who takes down tyrants

00:56:12.370 --> 00:56:14.560
because that's what
I'm going to become.

00:56:14.560 --> 00:56:17.020
And it's a very hollow
victory for him.

00:56:17.020 --> 00:56:18.990
And he has to live with that.

00:56:18.990 --> 00:56:19.930
And he has to go back.

00:56:19.930 --> 00:56:21.430
And we imagined
that was going to be

00:56:21.430 --> 00:56:24.940
the last episode of the
series, where if we did more,

00:56:24.940 --> 00:56:27.029
he would have to rebuild
that trust on Earth.

00:56:27.029 --> 00:56:29.320
And the only person who really
believes in him is Lois.

00:56:29.320 --> 00:56:32.620
And we thought, that's a great
place because he sort of lost

00:56:32.620 --> 00:56:33.940
the trust of Earth.

00:56:33.940 --> 00:56:35.736
But he's gained
the love of Lois.

00:56:35.736 --> 00:56:37.360
And we thought, if
we don't do anymore,

00:56:37.360 --> 00:56:39.210
this is a good
place to leave it.

